938
01:09:34,838 --> 01:09:36,254
For example,

939
01:09:36,961 --> 01:09:38,837
if the Kira's ability has been transferred to another person

940
01:09:39,659 --> 01:09:41,602
and the person has become the Third Kira

941
01:09:42,167 --> 01:09:44,625
and they've lost their memories

942
01:09:44,848 --> 01:09:46,483
It explains everything

943
01:09:47,327 --> 01:09:48,158
Even if you were right,

944
01:09:48,800 --> 01:09:50,433
there's no way to prove it

945
01:09:56,537 --> 01:09:57,305
Ryuzaki

946
01:10:00,579 --> 01:10:03,144
Why don't we try a different approach?

947
01:10:20,048 --> 01:10:21,813
How do you feel?

948
01:10:25,053 --> 01:10:26,803
Good, thanks

949
01:10:27,055 --> 01:10:28,962
I'm impressed with your courage

950
01:10:31,059 --> 01:10:34,380
Still, we have the evidence found in Amane's room

951
01:10:34,987 --> 01:10:39,300
You can't go outside until we solve the case

952
01:10:40,068 --> 01:10:41,873
If I have to stay here anyway

953
01:10:42,934 --> 01:10:45,824
Let me go back to the team and help you find Kira

954
01:10:46,074 --> 01:10:49,561
Yes, I was thinking about the exact same thing

955
01:10:50,614 --> 01:10:55,709
You have to stay with me all day and assist me

956
01:10:57,052 --> 01:10:58,452
Thanks, Ryuzaki

957
01:10:59,754 --> 01:11:01,280
Let's find Kira together

958
01:11:10,037 --> 01:11:11,132
I love you...

959
01:11:12,067 --> 01:11:13,591
Light

960
01:11:28,095 --> 01:11:29,797
Ms Wakita!
Are you okay?

961
01:11:29,785 --> 01:11:31,038
What happened to you?

962
01:11:31,723 --> 01:11:32,635
Get an ambulance!

963
01:11:39,060 --> 01:11:40,116
She's dead

964
01:11:41,433 --> 01:11:44,836
Her name is Wakita Masako and she was wanted for

965
01:11:45,066 --> 01:11:47,666
killing her colleague when she was working in a nightclub

966
01:11:48,837 --> 01:11:49,874
Is this another case

967
01:11:49,875 --> 01:11:52,338
of punishment from Kira?

968
01:11:53,074 --> 01:11:59,223
We found Wakita's address and tried to interview her

969
01:11:59,423 --> 01:12:01,215
but she died in front of us

970
01:12:01,967 --> 01:12:04,372
Ms. Takada, you must be shocked

971
01:12:05,053 --> 01:12:07,055
She did not have any health problem

972
01:12:07,055 --> 01:12:11,014
so it is natural to think that she was killed by Kira

973
01:12:12,451 --> 01:12:14,378
Now please look at this graph

974
01:12:15,353 --> 01:12:18,535
This is the result of a poll taken from 1000 people in Japan

975
01:12:19,067 --> 01:12:21,069
According to the result,

976
01:12:21,069 --> 01:12:23,550
60% of them are supporting Kira

977
01:12:23,550 --> 01:12:25,038
This is surprising isn't it?

978
01:12:25,073 --> 01:12:26,409
I don't think so

979
01:12:27,075 --> 01:12:29,077
Considering that the crime rate has been decreasing

980
01:12:31,884 --> 01:12:34,038
by the appearance of Kira, this result is expected

981
01:12:37,052 --> 01:12:39,020
Not bad

982
01:12:40,603 --> 01:12:43,430
This is a fact that Kira is fighting against evil

983
01:12:44,830 --> 01:12:47,007
What is the true justice?

984
01:12:47,953 --> 01:12:50,126
Does the police, or L, really can help us?

985
01:12:50,932 --> 01:12:52,585
Kira is trying to make us thing.

986
01:12:53,068 --> 01:12:54,659
She's good

987
01:12:57,072 --> 01:12:59,092
We can't blame her because

988
01:13:00,340 --> 01:13:03,536
We haven't found any clues to go on

989
01:13:05,080 --> 01:13:07,024
What's wrong Ryuzaki?
It's not like you

990
01:13:08,574 --> 01:13:10,542
Oh, great work!

991
01:13:12,105 --> 01:13:13,118
Thank you for supervising

992
01:13:13,406 --> 01:13:14,893
Your comments were witty

993
01:13:16,845 --> 01:13:17,843
Thank you so much!

994
01:13:19,010 --> 01:13:20,420
The director said that...

995
01:13:21,062 --> 01:13:22,966
you'd be a good anchor

996
01:13:23,642 --> 01:13:24,286
Really?

997
01:13:25,088 --> 01:13:28,222
for being critical towards the society through Kira's case...

998
01:13:28,645 --> 01:13:31,778
Your brave, intelligent attitude has attracted the viewers.

999
01:13:33,699 --> 01:13:35,841
You're becoming more attractive

1000
01:13:36,943 --> 01:13:37,930
Mr. Demegawa!

1001
01:13:41,026 --> 01:13:43,022
Could you ask your boss?

1002
01:13:44,032 --> 01:13:46,048
to spray pesticide in the studio

1003
01:13:46,620 --> 01:13:49,016
since a noisy bug's flying around here

1004
01:13:49,637 --> 01:13:50,786
Saeko!

1005
01:13:51,059 --> 01:13:52,391
Let's go have dinner?

1006
01:13:54,908 --> 01:13:55,737
Kiyomi

1007
01:13:56,655 --> 01:13:58,741
You know, each employee has an appropriate role, right?

1008
01:13:59,028 --> 01:14:00,367
What is your role, then?

1009
01:14:01,531 --> 01:14:03,824
No one's listening to your trashy comments!

1010
01:14:04,719 --> 01:14:05,444
Let's go

1011
01:14:12,080 --> 01:14:16,110
I say she's too fugly to be the anchor for our show!

1012
01:14:16,619 --> 01:14:17,711
Oh, come on

1013
01:14:18,053 --> 01:14:20,873
We employees can't say no to your boss, you know.

1014
01:14:21,590 --> 01:14:22,835
Are you kidding me?

1015
01:14:23,058 --> 01:14:25,821
You're the one who said no to your boss and showed Kira's video!

1016
01:14:26,906 --> 01:14:28,321
You slept with her, didn't you?

1017
01:14:29,578 --> 01:14:32,898
There's nobody but you who got a job by sleeping with me

1018
01:14:34,883 --> 01:14:35,863
Stop the car

1019
01:14:35,864 --> 01:14:36,832
Huh?

1020
01:14:37,072 --> 01:14:38,499
Stop the car now!

1021
01:14:47,465 --> 01:14:48,824
I'll never forgive her!

1022
01:14:50,074 --> 01:14:50,814
Hey, wait!

1023
01:14:51,803 --> 01:14:52,722
Calm down!

1024
01:14:54,236 --> 01:14:55,458
What's the matter with you!

1025
01:14:59,419 --> 01:15:01,594
